.TH "coresight_timeout" 9 "coresight_timeout" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
coresight_timeout \- loop until a bit has changed to a specific register state.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" coresight_timeout
.BI "(struct csdev_access *csa "  ","
.BI "u32 offset "  ","
.BI "int position "  ","
.BI "int value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "csa" 12
coresight device access for the device
.IP "offset" 12
Offset of the register from the base of the device.
.IP "position" 12
the position of the bit of interest.
.IP "value" 12
the value the bit should have.
.SH "RETURN"
0 as soon as the bit has taken the desired state or -EAGAIN if
TIMEOUT_US has elapsed, which ever happens first.
